The Kwara State Ministry of Agriculture and Rural Development, was thrown into mourning on Monday following the death of Dr Khalid Ibrahim Ndaman. He reportedly died in his office early Monday in Ilorin, the state capital. DAILY POST reports that Ndaman, until his death was the Director of Veterinary in the Ministry of Agriculture. Circumstances surrounding his death remained unclear at the time of this report. Reacting, the Spokesman of the state Police Command, SP Okasanmi Ajayi, told our DAILY POST that, ” It was a case of sudden and unnatural death, though no foul play suspected” Ajayi, however, added that the “case is undergoing investigation.”